<p class="">The right hon. Gentleman has stated exactly the position as I conceive it to be. When the proceedings are concluded and a valid decision has been given and confirmed, then, as a judge once said, the court itself is on trial and proper comment may be made. Until that stage, any comments on its merits are wholly improper and undesirable.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
